@Anita -- Thank you for mentioning that, as I also enjoyed their notes on XwordInfo today.  Usually, constructors' notes there are identical to their notes here, but occasionally constructors write different notes there, geared toward fellow constructors -- as Zhou and Kevin did today.  

It gave a fascinating look at how exacting the Times editing team is when it comes to accepting puzzles.  Anyone who's interested in that can read their notes by going to the puzzle on XwordInfo (the link is just below the constructor pictures), where you'll see the heading "Constructor Notes" above the puzzle.  

It made me feel better about the rejections I've gotten!

